{
  "video_id": "ogeGJS0GEF4",
  "title": "Why you should love statistics | Alan Smith",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12534.0,
      "end_time": 15630.0,
      "text": "Back in 2003,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15654.0,
      "end_time": 18163.0,
      "text": "the UK government carried out a survey."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19314.0,
      "end_time": 22463.0,
      "text": "And it was a survey that measured levels of numeracy"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 22487.0,
      "end_time": 23723.0,
      "text": "in the population."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23748.0,
      "end_time": 25391.0,
      "text": "And they were shocked to find out"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25415.0,
      "end_time": 28779.0,
      "text": "that for every 100 working age adults in the country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28803.0,
      "end_time": 32304.0,
      "text": "47 of them lacked Level 1 numeracy skills."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32712.000000000004,
      "end_time": 36824.0,
      "text": "Now, Level 1 numeracy skills -- that&#39;s low-end GCSE score."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37230.0,
      "end_time": 40477.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the ability to deal with fractions, percentages and decimals."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40502.0,
      "end_time": 45130.0,
      "text": "So this figure prompted a lot of hand-wringing in Whitehall."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 45154.0,
      "end_time": 46782.0,
      "text": "Policies were changed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 46806.0,
      "end_time": 48528.0,
      "text": "investments were made,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 48552.0,
      "end_time": 51589.0,
      "text": "and then they ran the survey again in 2011."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51614.0,
      "end_time": 53818.0,
      "text": "So can you guess what happened to this number?"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55841.0,
      "end_time": 57285.0,
      "text": "It went up to 49."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 57309.0,
      "end_time": 58757.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58782.0,
      "end_time": 61230.0,
      "text": "And in fact, when I reported this figure in the FT,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61255.0,
      "end_time": 62926.0,
      "text": "one of our readers joked and said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 62950.0,
      "end_time": 66711.0,
      "text": "\"This figure is only shocking to 51 percent of the population.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 66735.0,
      "end_time": 69210.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 69450.0,
      "end_time": 72202.0,
      "text": "But I preferred, actually, the reaction of a schoolchild"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 72226.0,
      "end_time": 75321.0,
      "text": "when I presented at a school this information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75345.0,
      "end_time": 76876.0,
      "text": "who raised their hand and said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 76900.0,
      "end_time": 79416.0,
      "text": "\"How do we know that the person who made that number"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79440.0,
      "end_time": 81255.0,
      "text": "isn&#39;t one of the 49 percent either?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 81279.0,
      "end_time": 82533.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 82557.0,
      "end_time": 86607.0,
      "text": "So clearly, there&#39;s a numeracy issue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 86631.0,
      "end_time": 88741.0,
      "text": "because these are important skills for life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 88765.0,
      "end_time": 92632.0,
      "text": "and a lot of the changes that we want to introduce in this century"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 92656.0,
      "end_time": 95970.0,
      "text": "involve us becoming more comfortable with numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 95121.0,
      "end_time": 96969.0,
      "text": "Now, it&#39;s not just an English problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 96993.0,
      "end_time": 101923.0,
      "text": "OECD this year released some figures looking at numeracy in young people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 101947.0,
      "end_time": 104727.0,
      "text": "and leading the way, the USA --"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 104751.0,
      "end_time": 109421.0,
      "text": "nearly 40 percent of young people in the US have low numeracy."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 109445.0,
      "end_time": 110741.0,
      "text": "Now, England is there too,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 110766.0,
      "end_time": 116299.0,
      "text": "but there are seven OECD countries with figures above 20 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 116323.0,
      "end_time": 119820.0,
      "text": "That is a problem, because it doesn&#39;t have to be that way."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119106.0,
      "end_time": 121113.0,
      "text": "If you look at the far end of this graph,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 121138.0,
      "end_time": 124980.0,
      "text": "you can see the Netherlands and Korea are in single figures."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 124122.0,
      "end_time": 128538.0,
      "text": "So there&#39;s definitely a numeracy problem that we want to address."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 129330.00000000001,
      "end_time": 132260.0,
      "text": "Now, as useful as studies like these are,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 132284.0,
      "end_time": 137684.0,
      "text": "I think we risk herding people inadvertently into one of two categories;"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 137708.0,
      "end_time": 139484.0,
      "text": "that there are two kinds of people:"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 139508.0,
      "end_time": 143857.0,
      "text": "those people that are comfortable with numbers, that can do numbers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 143881.0,
      "end_time": 146117.0,
      "text": "and the people who can&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 146141.0,
      "end_time": 148242.0,
      "text": "And what I&#39;m trying to talk about here today"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148266.0,
      "end_time": 151308.0,
      "text": "is to say that I believe that is a false dichotomy."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 151332.0,
      "end_time": 153200.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not an immutable pairing."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 153224.0,
      "end_time": 156872.0,
      "text": "I think you don&#39;t have to have tremendously high levels of numeracy"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 156896.0,
      "end_time": 158624.0,
      "text": "to be inspired by numbers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 158648.0,
      "end_time": 161757.0,
      "text": "and that should be the starting point to the journey ahead."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 162207.0,
      "end_time": 166518.0,
      "text": "And one of the ways in which we can begin that journey, for me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 166542.0,
      "end_time": 168268.0,
      "text": "is looking at statistics."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168292.0,
      "end_time": 171787.0,
      "text": "Now, I am the first to acknowledge that statistics has got somewhat"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171811.0,
      "end_time": 173129.0,
      "text": "of an image problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 173153.0,
      "end_time": 174200.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 174224.0,
      "end_time": 175756.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the part of mathematics"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 175780.0,
      "end_time": 178839.0,
      "text": "that even mathematicians don&#39;t particularly like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 178863.0,
      "end_time": 182875.0,
      "text": "because whereas the rest of maths is all about precision and certainty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 182899.0,
      "end_time": 185183.0,
      "text": "statistics is almost the reverse of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 185613.0,
      "end_time": 190268.0,
      "text": "But actually, I was a late convert to the world of statistics myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 190292.0,
      "end_time": 192374.0,
      "text": "If you&#39;d asked my undergraduate professors"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 192398.0,
      "end_time": 197156.0,
      "text": "what two subjects would I be least likely to excel in after university,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197181.0,
      "end_time": 199948.0,
      "text": "they&#39;d have told you statistics and computer programming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 199972.0,
      "end_time": 202911.0,
      "text": "and yet here I am, about to show you some statistical graphics"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 202935.0,
      "end_time": 204137.0,
      "text": "that I programmed."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 204565.0,
      "end_time": 206320.0,
      "text": "So what inspired that change in me?"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 206344.0,
      "end_time": 209992.0,
      "text": "What made me think that statistics was actually an interesting thing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 210160.0,
      "end_time": 212281.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really because statistics are about us."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 212689.0,
      "end_time": 215271.0,
      "text": "If you look at the etymology of the word statistics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 215295.0,
      "end_time": 217904.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s the science of dealing with data"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 217928.0,
      "end_time": 220358.0,
      "text": "about the state or the community that we live in."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 220382.0,
      "end_time": 223736.0,
      "text": "So statistics are about us as a group,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 223760.0,
      "end_time": 225435.0,
      "text": "not us as individuals."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 225459.0,
      "end_time": 226929.0,
      "text": "And I think as social animals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 226953.0,
      "end_time": 230897.0,
      "text": "we share this fascination about how we as individuals relate to our groups,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 230921.0,
      "end_time": 232309.0,
      "text": "to our peers."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 232333.0,
      "end_time": 235443.0,
      "text": "And statistics in this way are at their most powerful"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 235467.0,
      "end_time": 236768.0,
      "text": "when they surprise us."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 237297.0,
      "end_time": 240504.0,
      "text": "And there&#39;s been some really wonderful surveys carried out recently"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 240528.0,
      "end_time": 242242.0,
      "text": "by Ipsos MORI in the last few years."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 242266.0,
      "end_time": 244974.0,
      "text": "They did a survey of over 1,000 adults in the UK,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 244998.0,
      "end_time": 248778.0,
      "text": "and said, for every 100 people in England and Wales,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 248802.0,
      "end_time": 250672.0,
      "text": "how many of them are Muslim?"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 250696.0,
      "end_time": 253341.0,
      "text": "Now the average answer from this survey,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 253366.0,
      "end_time": 256778.0,
      "text": "which was supposed to be representative of the total population, was 24."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 256802.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260478.00000000003,
      "text": "That&#39;s what people thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 260502.0,
      "end_time": 264141.0,
      "text": "British people think 24 out of every 100 people in the country are Muslim."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 264165.0,
      "end_time": 268575.0,
      "text": "Now, official figures reveal that figure to be about five."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 269552.0,
      "end_time": 273539.0,
      "text": "So there&#39;s this big variation between what we think, our perception,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 273563.0,
      "end_time": 275601.0,
      "text": "and the reality as given by statistics."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 275625.0,
      "end_time": 277169.0,
      "text": "And I think that&#39;s interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 277193.0,
      "end_time": 280483.0,
      "text": "What could possibly be causing that misperception?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 281320.0,
      "end_time": 282885.0,
      "text": "And I was so thrilled with this study,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 282910.0,
      "end_time": 286390.0,
      "text": "I started to take questions out in presentations. I was referring to it."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 286414.0,
      "end_time": 287632.0,
      "text": "Now, I did a presentation"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 287656.0,
      "end_time": 289966.0,
      "text": "at St. Paul&#39;s School for Girls in Hammersmith,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 289990.0,
      "end_time": 292130.0,
      "text": "and I had an audience rather like this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 292154.0,
      "end_time": 296220.0,
      "text": "except it was comprised entirely of sixth-form girls."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 296460.0,
      "end_time": 298442.0,
      "text": "And I said, \"Girls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 299418.0,
      "end_time": 303961.0,
      "text": "how many teenage girls do you think the British public think"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 303985.0,
      "end_time": 305733.0,
      "text": "get pregnant every year?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 305757.0,
      "end_time": 308433.0,
      "text": "And the girls were apoplectic when I said"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 309273.0,
      "end_time": 313186.0,
      "text": "the British public think that 15 out of every 100 teenage girls"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 313210.0,
      "end_time": 314503.0,
      "text": "get pregnant in the year."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 315249.0,
      "end_time": 317480.0,
      "text": "And they had every right to be angry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 317504.0,
      "end_time": 320262.0,
      "text": "because in fact, I&#39;d have to have closer to 200 dots"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 320286.0,
      "end_time": 321856.0,
      "text": "before I could color one in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 321880.0,
      "end_time": 324395.0,
      "text": "in terms of what the official figures tell us."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 324419.0,
      "end_time": 328219.0,
      "text": "And rather like numeracy, this is not just an English problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 328243.0,
      "end_time": 332747.0,
      "text": "Ipsos MORI expanded the survey in recent years to go across the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 332771.0,
      "end_time": 335721.0,
      "text": "And so, they asked Saudi Arabians,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 335745.0,
      "end_time": 338266.0,
      "text": "for every 100 adults in your country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 338290.0,
      "end_time": 341163.0,
      "text": "how many of them are overweight or obese?"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 342346.0,
      "end_time": 347679.0,
      "text": "And the average answer from the Saudis was just over a quarter."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 348222.0,
      "end_time": 349424.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s what they thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 349448.0,
      "end_time": 352150.0,
      "text": "Just over a quarter of adults are overweight or obese."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 352400.0,
      "end_time": 356821.0,
      "text": "The official figures show, actually, it&#39;s nearer to three-quarters."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 356845.0,
      "end_time": 358301.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 358325.0,
      "end_time": 360616.0,
      "text": "So again, a big variation."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 360641.0,
      "end_time": 365870.0,
      "text": "And I love this one: they asked in Japan, they asked the Japanese,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 365111.0,
      "end_time": 367700.0,
      "text": "for every 100 Japanese people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 367950.0,
      "end_time": 369696.0,
      "text": "how many of them live in rural areas?"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 370341.0,
      "end_time": 375242.0,
      "text": "The average was about a 50-50 split, just over halfway."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 375266.0,
      "end_time": 379413.0,
      "text": "They thought 56 out of every 100 Japanese people lived in rural areas."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 379437.0,
      "end_time": 381124.0,
      "text": "The official figure is seven."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 382790.0,
      "end_time": 386529.0,
      "text": "So extraordinary variations, and surprising to some,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 386553.0,
      "end_time": 388942.0,
      "text": "but not surprising to people who have read the work"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 388966.0,
      "end_time": 393358.0,
      "text": "of Daniel Kahneman, for example, the Nobel-winning economist."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 393382.0,
      "end_time": 398474.0,
      "text": "He and his colleague, Amos Tversky, spent years researching this disjoint"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 398498.0,
      "end_time": 401643.0,
      "text": "between what people perceive and the reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 401667.0,
      "end_time": 405417.0,
      "text": "the fact that people are actually pretty poor intuitive statisticians."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 405442.0,
      "end_time": 407202.0,
      "text": "And there are many reasons for this."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 407226.0,
      "end_time": 410341.0,
      "text": "Individual experiences, certainly, can influence our perceptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 410365.0,
      "end_time": 414323.0,
      "text": "but so, too, can things like the media reporting things by exception,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 414347.0,
      "end_time": 416430.0,
      "text": "rather than what&#39;s normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 416675.0,
      "end_time": 418801.0,
      "text": "Kahneman had a nice way of referring to that."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 418825.0,
      "end_time": 420909.0,
      "text": "He said, \"We can be blind to the obvious\" --"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 420934.0,
      "end_time": 422572.0,
      "text": "so we&#39;ve got the numbers wrong --"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 422596.0,
      "end_time": 424918.0,
      "text": "\"but we can be blind to our blindness about it.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 424942.0,
      "end_time": 428208.0,
      "text": "And that has enormous repercussions for decision making."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 428232.0,
      "end_time": 431840.0,
      "text": "So at the statistics office while this was all going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 431108.0,
      "end_time": 433200.0,
      "text": "I thought this was really interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 433440.0,
      "end_time": 435540.0,
      "text": "I said, this is clearly a global problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 435780.0,
      "end_time": 437513.0,
      "text": "but maybe geography is the issue here."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 437537.0,
      "end_time": 441445.0,
      "text": "These were questions that were all about, how well do you know your country?"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 441470.0,
      "end_time": 445463.0,
      "text": "So in this case, it&#39;s how well do you know 64 million people?"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 445487.0,
      "end_time": 448219.0,
      "text": "Not very well, it turns out. I can&#39;t do that."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 448243.0,
      "end_time": 449567.0,
      "text": "So I had an idea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 449591.0,
      "end_time": 452714.0,
      "text": "which was to think about this same sort of approach"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 452738.0,
      "end_time": 454843.0,
      "text": "but to think about it in a very local sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 454867.0,
      "end_time": 456580.0,
      "text": "Is this a local?"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 456820.0,
      "end_time": 458220.0,
      "text": "If we reframe the questions and say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 458470.0,
      "end_time": 460169.0,
      "text": "how well do you know your local area,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 460193.0,
      "end_time": 462296.0,
      "text": "would your answers be any more accurate?"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 463637.0,
      "end_time": 465399.0,
      "text": "So I devised a quiz:"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 465423.0,
      "end_time": 467282.0,
      "text": "How well do you know your area?"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 468274.0,
      "end_time": 470163.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a simple Web app."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 470187.0,
      "end_time": 471370.0,
      "text": "You put in a post code"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 471394.0,
      "end_time": 474101.0,
      "text": "and then it will ask you questions based on census data"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 474125.0,
      "end_time": 475664.0,
      "text": "for your local area."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 476125.0,
      "end_time": 478248.0,
      "text": "And I was very conscious in designing this."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 478272.0,
      "end_time": 482381.0,
      "text": "I wanted to make it open to the widest possible range of people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 482405.0,
      "end_time": 485232.0,
      "text": "not just the 49 percent who can get the numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 485257.0,
      "end_time": 487120.0,
      "text": "I wanted everyone to engage with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 487360.0,
      "end_time": 488561.0,
      "text": "So for the design of the quiz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 488585.0,
      "end_time": 492200.0,
      "text": "I was inspired by the isotypes"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 492224.0,
      "end_time": 494825.0,
      "text": "of Otto Neurath from the 1920s and &#39;30s."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 494850.0,
      "end_time": 499198.0,
      "text": "Now, these are methods for representing numbers"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 499222.0,
      "end_time": 500995.0,
      "text": "using repeating icons."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 501460.0,
      "end_time": 504625.0,
      "text": "And the numbers are there, but they sit in the background."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 504649.0,
      "end_time": 507372.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s a great way of representing quantity"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 507396.0,
      "end_time": 510380.0,
      "text": "without resorting to using terms like \"percentage,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 510404.0,
      "end_time": 511634.0,
      "text": "\"fractions\" and \"ratios.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 511658.0,
      "end_time": 513360.0,
      "text": "So here&#39;s the quiz."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 514130.0,
      "end_time": 515777.0,
      "text": "The layout of the quiz is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 515801.00000000006,
      "end_time": 518620.00000000006,
      "text": "you have your repeating icons on the left-hand side there,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 518644.0,
      "end_time": 521767.0,
      "text": "and a map showing you the area we&#39;re asking you questions about"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 521791.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522958.00000000006,
      "text": "on the right-hand side."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 522982.0,
      "end_time": 524262.0,
      "text": "There are seven questions."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 524287.00000000006,
      "end_time": 528180.0,
      "text": "Each question, there&#39;s a possible answer between zero and a hundred,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 528204.0,
      "end_time": 529553.0,
      "text": "and at the end of the quiz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 529577.0,
      "end_time": 532795.0,
      "text": "you get an overall score between zero and a hundred."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 532819.0,
      "end_time": 534902.0,
      "text": "And so because this is TEDxExeter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 534927.0,
      "end_time": 537252.0,
      "text": "I thought we would have a quick look at the quiz"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 537276.0,
      "end_time": 539584.0,
      "text": "for the first few questions of Exeter."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 539609.0,
      "end_time": 541140.0,
      "text": "And so the first question is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 541380.0,
      "end_time": 544300.0,
      "text": "For every 100 people, how many are aged under 16?"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 544604.0,
      "end_time": 548204.0,
      "text": "Now, I don&#39;t know Exeter very well at all, so I had a guess at this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 548228.0,
      "end_time": 550789.0,
      "text": "but it gives you an idea of how this quiz works."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 550813.0,
      "end_time": 554519.0,
      "text": "You drag the slider to highlight your icons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 554543.0,
      "end_time": 556778.0,
      "text": "and then just click \"Submit\" to answer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 556802.0,
      "end_time": 560465.0,
      "text": "and we animate away the difference between your answer and reality."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 560489.0,
      "end_time": 564564.0,
      "text": "And it turns out, I was a pretty terrible guess: five."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 564969.0,
      "end_time": 566393.0,
      "text": "How about the next question?"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 566417.0,
      "end_time": 568573.0,
      "text": "This is asking about what the average age is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 568597.0,
      "end_time": 571420.0,
      "text": "so the age at which half the population are younger"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 571660.0,
      "end_time": 572740.0,
      "text": "and half the population are older."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 572764.0,
      "end_time": 576114.0,
      "text": "And I thought 35 -- that sounds middle-aged to me."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 576138.0,
      "end_time": 577581.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 580260.0,
      "end_time": 582132.0,
      "text": "Actually, in Exeter, it&#39;s incredibly young,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 582156.0,
      "end_time": 586694.0,
      "text": "and I had underestimated the impact of the university in this area."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 586718.0,
      "end_time": 588748.0,
      "text": "The questions get harder as you go through."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 588773.0,
      "end_time": 591156.0,
      "text": "So this one&#39;s now asking about homeownership:"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 591775.0,
      "end_time": 595473.0,
      "text": "For every 100 households, how many are owned with a mortgage or loan?"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 595498.0,
      "end_time": 596778.0,
      "text": "And I hedged my bets here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 596802.0,
      "end_time": 599900.0,
      "text": "because I didn&#39;t want to be more than 50 out on the answer."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 599924.0,
      "end_time": 601944.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 601968.0,
      "end_time": 604434.0,
      "text": "And actually, these get harder, these questions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 604458.0,
      "end_time": 607317.0,
      "text": "because when you&#39;re in an area, when you&#39;re in a community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 607341.0,
      "end_time": 612591.0,
      "text": "things like age -- there are clues to whether a population is old or young."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 612615.0,
      "end_time": 614960.0,
      "text": "Just by looking around the area, you can see it."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 614984.0,
      "end_time": 618375.0,
      "text": "Something like homeownership is much more difficult to see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 618399.0,
      "end_time": 621700.0,
      "text": "so we revert to our own heuristics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 621310.0,
      "end_time": 625482.0,
      "text": "our own biases about how many people we think own their own homes."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 625506.0,
      "end_time": 629156.0,
      "text": "Now the truth is, when we published this quiz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 629180.0,
      "end_time": 632715.0,
      "text": "the census data that it&#39;s based on was already a few years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 632740.0,
      "end_time": 636309.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve had online applications that allow you to put in a post code"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 636333.0,
      "end_time": 638427.0,
      "text": "and get statistics back for years."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 638451.0,
      "end_time": 639640.0,
      "text": "So in some senses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 639664.0,
      "end_time": 643213.0,
      "text": "this was all a little bit old and not necessarily new."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 643237.0,
      "end_time": 646876.0,
      "text": "But I was interested to see what reaction we might get"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 646900.0,
      "end_time": 649617.0,
      "text": "by gamifying the data in the way that we have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 649641.0,
      "end_time": 651480.0,
      "text": "by using animation"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 651720.0,
      "end_time": 654820.0,
      "text": "and playing on the fact that people have their own preconceptions."
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 655328.0,
      "end_time": 658911.0,
      "text": "It turns out, the reaction was, um ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 660148.0,
      "end_time": 662760.0,
      "text": "was more than I could have hoped for."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 662100.0,
      "end_time": 665481.0,
      "text": "It was a long-held ambition of mine to bring down a statistics website"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 665505.0,
      "end_time": 666913.0,
      "text": "due to public demand."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 666937.0,
      "end_time": 668737.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 668761.0,
      "end_time": 672225.0,
      "text": "This URL contains the words \"statistics,\" \"gov\" and \"UK,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 672249.0,
      "end_time": 675491.0,
      "text": "which are three of people&#39;s least favorite words in a URL."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 675515.0,
      "end_time": 679500.0,
      "text": "And the amazing thing about this was that the website came down"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 679524.0,
      "end_time": 681617.0,
      "text": "at quarter to 10 at night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 681641.0,
      "end_time": 684852.0,
      "text": "because people were actually engaging with this data"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 684876.0,
      "end_time": 686415.0,
      "text": "of their own free will,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 686439.0,
      "end_time": 688473.0,
      "text": "using their own personal time."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 688498.0,
      "end_time": 690985.0,
      "text": "I was very interested to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 691900.0,
      "end_time": 694722.0,
      "text": "that we got something like a quarter of a million people"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 694746.0,
      "end_time": 698180.0,
      "text": "playing the quiz within the space of 48 hours of launching it."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 698420.0,
      "end_time": 701969.0,
      "text": "And it sparked an enormous discussion online, on social media,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 701993.0,
      "end_time": 704300.0,
      "text": "which was largely dominated"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 704540.0,
      "end_time": 708470.0,
      "text": "by people having fun with their misconceptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 708710.0,
      "end_time": 711130.0,
      "text": "which is something that I couldn&#39;t have hoped for any better,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 711154.0,
      "end_time": 712314.0,
      "text": "in some respects."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 712338.0,
      "end_time": 715564.0,
      "text": "I also liked the fact that people started sending it to politicians."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 715588.0,
      "end_time": 718177.0,
      "text": "How well do you know the area you claim to represent?"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 718201.0,
      "end_time": 719363.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 719387.0,
      "end_time": 720946.0,
      "text": "And then just to finish,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 721812.0,
      "end_time": 724142.0,
      "text": "going back to the two kinds of people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 724166.0,
      "end_time": 726423.0,
      "text": "I thought it would be really interesting to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 726447.0,
      "end_time": 729262.0,
      "text": "how people who are good with numbers would do on this quiz."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 729286.0,
      "end_time": 732301.0,
      "text": "The national statistician of England and Wales, John Pullinger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 732326.0,
      "end_time": 734399.0,
      "text": "you would expect he would be pretty good."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 735344.0,
      "end_time": 737793.0,
      "text": "He got 44 for his own area."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 737817.0,
      "end_time": 740285.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 740309.0,
      "end_time": 745257.0,
      "text": "Jeremy Paxman -- admittedly, after a glass of wine -- 36."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 745871.0,
      "end_time": 747332.0,
      "text": "Even worse."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 747356.0,
      "end_time": 750557.0,
      "text": "It just shows you that the numbers can inspire us all."
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 750581.0,
      "end_time": 751841.0,
      "text": "They can surprise us all."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 751865.0,
      "end_time": 753904.0,
      "text": "So very often, we talk about statistics"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 753928.0,
      "end_time": 755890.0,
      "text": "as being the science of uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 755914.0,
      "end_time": 757696.0,
      "text": "My parting thought for today is:"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 757720.0,
      "end_time": 760755.0,
      "text": "actually, statistics is the science of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 760779.0,
      "end_time": 763567.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s why we should be fascinated by numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 763591.0,
      "end_time": 764781.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 764805.0,
      "end_time": 768582.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}